<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08125i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08125i">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08125i"> 125(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> God penetrates ear, BVM</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Redeemer could not take on a genuine human body, because He would thereby have come under the control of the evil principle. His body was, therefore, of celestial essence, and with it He penetrated the ear of Mary. <small> <a name="CECRA" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CECRA"><cite title="source">&ldquo;Coemgen&rdquo;, &ldquo;Rosary&rdquo; and &ldquo;Albigenses&rdquo;</cite></a> <cite a>Catholic Encyclopaedia</cite></a> (1911) I, &lsquo;Albigenses&rsquo; 268a</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
